If you feel the need to be political, or think politics are required to counter existing politics, may I offer a suggestion? Work your politics into your stories, properly. Not in a direct or obvious at all way, but let them be the undercurrent. J.R.R. Tolkein did this extremely well with LOTR and Christianity, the books are deeply Christian, but don't show it. Don't tell people what your politics are, or how you think things should be, SHOW them, demonstrate how your politics works properly, and make a good story while you're at it. That's far more persuasive than spastic arguments.
